This repository is a from-scratch Rust reimplementation of a TypeScript steno-DSL compiler: `crates/steno` parses `dict.steno` and emits four artifacts under `out/` (two Plover dictionaries, a stroke→token table, and an LSP-snippet table) via three binaries. Depending on the repo root gets you either the Rust library/binaries in `crates/`, the `dict.steno` source fixture itself, the `nvim/` Lua consumer plugin, or the Layer-1 CI gate in `scripts/`; nothing outside `crates/steno`'s own binaries writes to `out/`.

`dict.steno` is the single normative fixture shared by three otherwise-independent subtrees: `crates/steno` parses and tests against it directly (never mutating it), `docs/steno-format.md` describes its grammar and directive semantics, and `docs/porting-notes.md` pins specific corpus states in it (`STKWR-FB`, `STKWR-LT`) that must not regress toward TS parity. A change to any `%`-operator or directive in `dict.steno` requires checking both `crates/steno/src/parse.rs` and `docs/steno-format.md` for drift — the docs explicitly cede final authority to the Rust source when the two disagree. `docs/pipeline.md` separately governs the module-dependency direction (`parse → expand → {editor, render